obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (12850)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12850&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Protection of Children`
  line `from Sexual Offences Act, 2012.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India, ^1***.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-10-2019).`
  line
  line `2. 14th November, 2012, vide notification No.S.O. 2705 (E), dated 9th November, 2012, see Gazette of India Extraordinary, Part`
  line `II, sec. 3(ii)/.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (12851)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12851&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires, --`
  line
  line `(a) "aggravated penetrative sexual assault" has the same meaning as assigned to it in section 5;`
  line
  line `(b) "aggravated sexual assault" has the same meaning as assigned to it in section 9;`
  line
  line `(c) "armed forces or security forces" means armed forces of the Union or security forces or police`
  line `forces, as specified in the Schedule;`
  line
  line `(d) "child" means any person below the age of eighteen years;`
  line
  line `^1[(da) "child pornography" means any visual depiction of sexually explicit conduct involving a`
  line `child which include photograph, video, digital or computer generated image indistinguishable from an`
  line `actual child and image created, adapted, or modified, but appear to depict a child;]`
  line
  line `(e) "domestic relationship" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause (f) of section 2`
  line `of the Protection of Women from Domestic Violence Act, 2005 (43 of 2005);`
  line
  line `(f) "penetrative sexual assault" has the same meaning as assigned to it in section 3;`
  line
  line `(g) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) "religious institution" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in the Religious`
  line `Institutions (Prevention of Misuse) Act, 1988 (41 of 1988).`
  line
  line `(i) "sexual assault" has the same meaning as assigned to it in section 7;`
  line
  line `(j) "sexual harassment" has the same meaning as assigned to it in section 11;`
  line
  line `(k) "shared household" means a household where the person charged with the offence lives or has`
  line `lived at any time in a domestic relationship with the child;`
  line
  line `(l) "Special Court" means a court designated as such under section 28;`
  line
  line `(m) "Special Public Prosecutor" means a Public Prosecutor appointed under section 32.`
  line
  line `(2) The words and expressions used herein and not defined but defined in the Indian Penal Code`
  line `(45 of 1860), the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974),`
  line `^2[the Juvenile Justice (Care and`
  line `Protection of Children) Act, 2015 (2 of 2016)] and the Information Technology Act, 2000 (21 of 2000)`
  line `shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in the said Codes or the Acts.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 25 of 2019, s. 2 (w.e.f. 16-08-2019).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "the Juvenile Justice (Care and Protection of Children) Act, 2000 (56 of 2000)" (w.e.f. 16-08-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (12852)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Penetrative sexual assault.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12852&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `A person is said to commit "penetrative sexual assault" if--`
  line
  line `(a) he penetrates his penis, to any extent, into the vagina, mouth, urethra or anus of a child or`
  line `makes the child to do so with him or any other person; or`
  line
  line `(b) he inserts, to any extent, any object or a part of the body, not being the penis, into the vagina,`
  line `the urethra or anus of the child or makes the child to do so with him or any other person; or`
  line
  line `(c) he manipulates any part of the body of the child so as to cause penetration into the vagina,`
  line `urethra, anus or any part of body of the child or makes the child to do so with him or any other`
  line `person; or`
  line
  line `(d) he applies his mouth to the penis, vagina, anus, urethra of the child or makes the child to do so`
  line `to such person or any other person.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (12853)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Punishment for penetrative sexual assault.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12853&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] Whoever commits penetrative sexual assault`
  line `shall be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which shall not be less than ^2[ten`
  line `years] but which may extend to imprisonment for life, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `^3[(2) Whoever commits penetrative sexual assault on a child below sixteen years of age shall be`
  line `punished with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than twenty years, but which may extend`
  line `to imprisonment for life, which shall mean imprisonment for the remainder of natural life of that person`
  line `and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(3) The fine imposed under sub-section (1) shall be just and reasonable and paid to the victim to meet`
  line `the medical expenses and rehabilitation of such victim.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 4 renumbered as section 4(1) thereof by s. 3, ibid (w.e.f. 16-08-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "seven years" (w.e.f. 16-08-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 16-08-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (12854)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Aggravated penetrative sexual assault.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12854&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(a) Whoever, being a police officer, commits`
  line `penetrative sexual assault on a child --`
  line
  line `(i) within the limits of the police station or premises at which he is appointed; or`
  line
  line `(ii) in the premises of any station house, whether or not situated in the police station, to which he`
  line `is appointed; or`
  line
  line `(iii) in the course of his duties or otherwise; or`
  line
  line `(iv) where he is known as, or identified as, a police officer; or`
  line
  line `(b) whoever being a member of the armed forces or security forces commits penetrative sexual assault`
  line `on a child--`
  line
  line `(i) within the limits of the area to which the person is deployed; or`
  line
  line `(ii) in any areas under the command of the forces or armed forces; or`
  line
  line `(iii) in the course of his duties or otherwise; or`
  line
  line `(iv) where the said person is known or identified as a member of the security or armed forces; or`
  line
  line `(c) whoever being a public servant commits penetrative sexual assault on a child; or`
  line
  line `(d) whoever being on the management or on the staff of a jail, remand home, protection home,`
  line `observation home, or other place of custody or care and protection established by or under any law for the`
  line `time being in force, commits penetrative sexual assault on a child, being inmate of such jail, remand`
  line `home, protection home, observation home, or other place of custody or care and protection; or`
  line
  line `(e) whoever being on the management or staff of a hospital, whether Government or private, commits`
  line `penetrative sexual assault on a child in that hospital; or`
  line
  line `(f) whoever being on the management or staff of an educational institution or religious institution,`
  line `commits penetrative sexual assault on a child in that institution; or`
  line
  line `(g) whoever commits gang penetrative sexual assault on a child.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- When a child is subjected to sexual assault by one or more persons of a group in`
  line `furtherance of their common intention, each of such persons shall be deemed to have committed gang`
  line `penetrative sexual assault within the meaning of this clause and each of such person shall be liable for that`
  line `act in the same manner as if it were done by him alone; or`
  line
  line `(h) whoever commits penetrative sexual assault on a child using deadly weapons, fire, heated`
  line `substance or corrosive substance; or`
  line
  line `(i) whoever commits penetrative sexual assault causing grievous hurt or causing bodily harm and`
  line `injury or injury to the sexual organs of the child; or`
  line
  line `(j) whoever commits penetrative sexual assault on a child, which--`
  line
  line `(i) physically incapacitates the child or causes the child to become mentally ill as defined under`
  line `clause (l) of section 2 of the Mental Health Act, 1987 (14 of 1987) or causes impairment of any kind`
  line `so as to render the child unable to perform regular tasks, temporarily or permanently; ^1***`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of female child, makes the child pregnant as a consequence of sexual assault;`
  line
  line `(iii) inflicts the child with Human Immunodeficiency Virus or any other life threatening disease`
  line `or Infection which may either temporarily or permanently impair the child by rendering him`
  line `physically incapacitated, or mentally ill to perform regular tasks; ^1***`
  line
  line `^2[(iv) causes death of the child; or]`
  line
  line `(k) whoever, taking advantage of a child's mental or physical disability, commits penetrative sexual`
  line `assault on the child; or`
  line
  line `(l) whoever commits penetrative sexual assault on the child more than once or repeatedly; or`
  line
  line `(m) whoever commits penetrative sexual assault on a child below twelve years; or`
  line
  line `(n) whoever being a relative of the child through blood or adoption or marriage or guardianship or in`
  line `foster care or having a domestic relationship with a parent of the child or who is living in the same or`
  line `shared household with the child, commits penetrative sexual assault on such child; or`
  line
  line `(o) whoever being, in the ownership, or management, or staff, of any institution providing services to`
  line `the child, commits penetrative sexual assault on the child; or`
  line
  line `(p) whoever being in a position of trust or authority of a child commits penetrative sexual assault on`
  line `the child in an institution or home of the child or anywhere else; or`
  line
  line `(q) whoever commits penetrative sexual assault on a child knowing the child is pregnant; or`
  line
  line `(r) whoever commits penetrative sexual assault on a child and attempts to murder the child; or`
  line
  line `(s) whoever commits penetrative sexual assault on a child in the course of ^3[communal or sectarian`
  line `violence or during any natural calamity or in similar situations]; or`
  line
  line `(t) whoever commits penetrative sexual assault on a child and who has been previously convicted of`
  line `having committed any offence under this Act or any sexual offence punishable under any other law for`
  line `the time being in force; or`
  line
  line `(u) whoever commits penetrative sexual assault on a child and makes the child to strip or parade`
  line `naked in public,`
  line `is said to commit aggravated penetrative sexual assault.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word or omitted by Act 25 of 2019, s. 4 (w.e.f. 16-08-2019).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 4, ibid (w.e.f. 16-08-2019).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 2019, s. 4, for communal or sectarian violence (w.e.f. 16-08-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (12855)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Punishment for aggravated penetrative sexual assault.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for section 6 (w.e.f. 16-08-2019).br`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12855&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `^1[6. Punishment for aggravated penetrative sexual assault.-- (1) Whoever commits aggravated`
  line `penetrative sexual assault shall be punished with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less`
  line `than twenty years, but which may extend to imprisonment for life, which shall mean imprisonment for the`
  line `remainder of natural life of that person and shall also be liable to fine, or with death.`
  line
  line `(2) The fine imposed under sub-section (1) shall be just and reasonable and paid to the victim to meet`
  line `the medical expenses and rehabilitation of such victim.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (12856)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Sexual assault.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12856&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, with sexual intent touches the vagina, penis, anus or breast of the child`
  line `or makes the child touch the vagina, penis, anus or breast of such person or any other person, or does any`
  line `other act with sexual intent which involves physical contact without penetration is said to commit sexual`
  line assault.
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (12857)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Punishment for sexual assault.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12857&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, commits sexual assault, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description for a term which shall not be less than three years but which may`
  line `extend to five years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (12858)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Aggravated sexual assault.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12858&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(a) Whoever, being a police officer, commits sexual assault on a`
  line child--
  line
  line `(i) within the limits of the police station or premises where he is appointed; or`
  line
  line `(ii) in the premises of any station house whether or not situated in the police station to which he is`
  line `appointed; or`
  line
  line `(iii) in the course of his duties or otherwise; or`
  line
  line `(iv) where he is known as, or identified as a police officer; or`
  line
  line `(b) whoever, being a member of the armed forces or security forces, commits sexual assault on a`
  line child--
  line
  line `(i) within the limits of the area to which the person is deployed; or`
  line
  line `(ii) in any areas under the command of the security or armed forces; or`
  line
  line `(iii) in the course of his duties or otherwise; or`
  line
  line `(iv) where he is known or identified as a member of the security or armed forces; or`
  line
  line `(c) whoever being a public servant commits sexual assault on a child; or`
  line
  line `(d) whoever being on the management or on the staff of a jail, or remand home or protection home or`
  line `observation home, or other place of custody or care and protection established by or under any law for the`
  line `time being in force commits sexual assault on a child being inmate of such jail or remand home or`
  line `protection home or observation home or other place of custody or care and protection; or`
  line
  line `(e) whoever being on the management or staff of a hospital, whether Government or private, commits`
  line `sexual assault on a child in that hospital; or`
  line
  line `(f) whoever being on the management or staff of an educational institution or religious institution,`
  line `commits sexual assault on a child in that institution; or`
  line
  line `(g) whoever commits gang sexual assault on a child.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- when a child is subjected to sexual assault by one or more persons of a group in`
  line `furtherance of their common intention, each of such persons shall be deemed to have committed gang`
  line `sexual assault within the meaning of this clause and each of such person shall be liable for that act in the`
  line `same manner as if it were done by him alone; or`
  line
  line `(h) whoever commits sexual assault on a child using deadly weapons, fire, heated substance or`
  line `corrosive substance; or`
  line
  line `(i) whoever commits sexual assault causing grievous hurt or causing bodily harm and injury or injury`
  line `to the sexual organs of the child; or`
  line `(j) whoever commits sexual assault on a child, which--`
  line
  line `(i) physically incapacitates the child or causes the child to become mentally ill as defined under`
  line `clause (l) of section 2of the Mental Health Act, 1987 (14 of 1987) or causes impairment of any kind`
  line `so as to render the child unable to perform regular tasks, temporarily or permanently; or`
  line
  line `(ii) inflicts the child with Human Immunodeficiency Virus or any other life threatening disease or`
  line `infection which may either temporarily or permanently impair the child by rendering him physically`
  line `incapacitated, or mentally ill to perform regular tasks; or`
  line
  line `(k) whoever, taking advantage of a childs mental or physical disability, commits sexual assault on the`
  line `child; or`
  line
  line `(l) whoever commits sexual assault on the child more than once or repeatedly; or`
  line
  line `(m) whoever commits sexual assault on a child below twelve years; or`
  line
  line `(n) whoever, being a relative of the child through blood or adoption or marriage or guardianship or in`
  line `foster care, or having domestic relationship with a parent of the child, or who is living in the same or`
  line `shared household with the child, commits sexual assault on such child; or`
  line
  line `(o) whoever, being in the ownership or management or staff, of any institution providing services to`
  line `the child, commits sexual assault on the child in such institution; or`
  line
  line `(p) whoever, being in a position of trust or authority of a child, commits sexual assault on the child in`
  line `an institution or home of the child or anywhere else; or`
  line
  line `(q) whoever commits sexual assault on a child knowing the child is pregnant; or`
  line
  line `(r) whoever commits sexual assault on a child and attempts to murder the child; or`
  line
  line `(s) whoever commits sexual assault on a child in the course of ^1[ communal or sectarian violence or`
  line `during any natural calamity or in any similar situations]; or`
  line
  line `(t) whoever commits sexual assault on a child and who has been previously convicted of having`
  line `committed any offence under this Act or any sexual offence punishable under any other law for the time`
  line `being in force; or`
  line `(u) whoever commits sexual assault on a child and makes the child to strip or parade naked in public,`
  line `is said to commit aggravated sexual assault.`
  line
  line `^2[(v) whoever persuades, induces, entices or coerces a child to get administered or administers or`
  line `direct anyone to administer, help in getting administered any drug or hormone or any chemical substance,`
  line `to a child with the intent that such child attains early sexual maturity.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2019, s. 6, for "communal or sectarian violence" (w.e.f. 16-08-2019).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 16-08-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (12859)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Punishment for aggravated sexual assault.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12859&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, commits aggravated sexual assault shall`
  line `be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which shall not be less than five years but`
  line `which may extend to seven years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (12860)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Sexual harassment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12860&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `A person is said to commit sexual harassment upon a child when such`
  line `person with sexual intent,--`
  line
  line `(i) utters any word or makes any sound, or makes any gesture or exhibits any object or part of`
  line `body with the intention that such word or sound shall be heard, or such gesture or object or part of`
  line `body shall be seen by the child; or`
  line
  line `(ii) makes a child exhibit his body or any part of his body so as it is seen by such person or any`
  line `other person; or`
  line
  line `(iii) shows any object to a child in any form or media for pornographic purposes; or`
  line
  line `(iv) repeatedly or constantly follows or watches or contacts a child either directly or through`
  line `electronic, digital or any other means; or`
  line
  line `(v) threatens to use, in any form of media, a real or fabricated depiction through electronic, film`
  line `or digital or any other mode, of any part of the body of the child or the involvement of the child in a`
  line `sexual act; or`
  line
  line `(vi) entices a child for pornographic purposes or gives gratification therefor.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--Any question which involves '[sexual intent" shall be a question of fact.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (12861)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Punishment for sexual harassment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12861&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, commits sexual harassment upon a child shall`
  line `be punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend to three years and shall`
  line `also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (12862)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Use of child for pornographic purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12862&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, uses a child in any form of media`
  line `(including programme or advertisement telecast by television channels or internet or any other electronic`
  line `form or printed form, whether or not such programme or advertisement is intended for personal use or for`
  line `distribution), for the purposes of sexual gratification, which includes--`
  line
  line `(a) representation of the sexual organs of a child;`
  line
  line `(b) usage of a child engaged in real or simulated sexual acts (with or without penetration);`
  line
  line `(c) the indecent or obscene representation of a child,`
  line
  line `shall be guilty of the offence of using a child for pornographic purposes.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the expression ''use a child'' shall include involving a`
  line `child through any medium like print, electronic, computer or any other technology for preparation,`
  line `production, offering, transmitting, publishing, facilitation and distribution of the pornographic material.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (12863)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Punishment for using child for pornographic purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2019, s. 7, for section 14 (w.e.f. 16-08-2019)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12863&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `^1[14. Punishment for using child for pornographic purposes.-- (1) Whoever uses a child or`
  line `children for pornographic purposes shall be punished with imprisonment for a term which shall not be`
  line `less than five years and shall also be liable to fine and in the event of second or subsequent conviction`
  line `with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than seven years and also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever using a child or children for pornographic purposes under sub-section (1), commits an`
  line `offence referred to in section 3 or section 5 or section 7 or section 9 by directly participating in such`
  line `pornographic acts, shall be punished for the said offences also under section 4, section 6, section 8 and`
  line `section 10, respectively, in addition to the punishment provided in sub-section (1).]`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (12864)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Punishment for storage of pornographic material involving child.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for section 15 (w.e.f. 16-08-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12864&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `^1[15. Punishment for storage of pornographic material involving child.-- (1) Any person, who`
  line `stores or possesses pornographic material in any form involving a child, but fails to delete or destroy or`
  line `report the same to the designated authority, as may be prescribed, with an intention to share or transmit`
  line `child pornography, shall be liable to fine not less than five thousand rupees and in the event of second or`
  line `subsequent offence, with fine which shall not be less than ten thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person, who stores or possesses pornographic material in any form involving a child for`
  line `transmitting or propagating or displaying or distributing in any manner at any time except for the purpose`
  line `of reporting, as may be prescribed, or for use as evidence in court, shall be punished with imprisonment`
  line `of either description which may extend to three years, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person, who stores or possesses pornographic material in any form involving a child for`
  line `commercial purpose shall be punished on the first conviction with imprisonment of either description`
  line `which shall not be less than three years which may extend to five years, or with fine, or with both and in`
  line `the event of second or subsequent conviction, with imprisonment of either description which shall not be`
  line `less than five years which may extend to seven years and shall also be liable to fine.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (12865)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Abetment of an offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12865&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `A person abets an offence, who--`
  line
  line `First.-- Instigates any person to do that offence; or`
  line
  line `Secondly.-- Engages with one or more other person or persons in any conspiracy for the doing of`
  line `that offence, if an act or illegal omission takes place in pursuance of that conspiracy, and in order to`
  line `the doing of that offence; or`
  line
  line `Thirdly.-- Intentionally aids, by any act or illegal omission, the doing of that offence.`
  line
  line `Explanation I.--A person who, by wilful misrepresentation, or by wilful concealment of a material`
  line `fact, which he is bound to disclose, voluntarily causes or procures, or attempts to cause or procure a thing`
  line `to be done, is said to instigate the doing of that offence.`
  line
  line `Explanation II.--Whoever, either prior to or at the time of commission of an act, does anything in`
  line `order to facilitate the commission of that act, and thereby facilitates the commission thereof, is said to aid`
  line `the doing of that act.`
  line
  line `Explanation III.--Whoever employ, harbours, receives or transports a child, by means of threat or use`
  line `of force or other forms of coercion, abduction, fraud, deception, abuse of power or of a position,`
  line `vulnerability or the giving or receiving of payments or benefits to achieve the consent of a person having`
  line `control over another person, for the purpose of any offence under this Act, is said to aid the doing of that`
  line act.
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (12866)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Punishment for abetment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12866&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Whoever abets any offence under this Act, if the act abetted is`
  line `committed in consequence of the abetment, shall be punished with punishment provided for that offence.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- An act or offence is said to be committed in consequence of abetment, when it is`
  line `committed in consequence of the instigation, or in pursuance of the conspiracy or with the aid, which`
  line `constitutes the abetment.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (12867)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Punishment for attempt to commit an offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12867&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Whoever attempts to commit any offence`
  line `punishable under this Act or to cause such an offence to be committed, and in such attempt, does any act`
  line `towards the commission of the offence, shall be punished with imprisonment of any description provided`
  line `for the offence, for a term which may extend to one half of the imprisonment for life or, as the case may`
  line `be, one-half of the longest term of imprisonment provided for that offence or with fine or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (12868)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Reporting of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12868&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) any person (including the child), who has apprehension that an offence under`
  line `this Act is likely to be committed or has knowledge that such an offence has been committed, he shall`
  line `provide such information to,--`
  line
  line `(a) the Special Juvenile Police Unit; or`
  line
  line `(b) the local police.`
  line
  line `(2) Every report given under sub-section (1) shall be--`
  line
  line `(a) ascribed an entry number and recorded in writing;`
  line
  line `(b) be read over to the informant;`
  line
  line `(c) shall be entered in a book to be kept by the Police Unit.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the report under sub-section (1) is given by a child, the same shall be recorded under subsection`
  line `(2) in a simple language so that the child understands contents being recorded.`
  line
  line `(4) In case contents are being recorded in the language not understood by the child or wherever it is`
  line `deemed necessary, a translator or an interpreter, having such qualifications, experience and on payment of`
  line `such fees as may be prescribed, shall be provided to the child if he fails to understand the same.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the Special Juvenile Police Unit or local police is satisfied that the child against whom an`
  line `offence has been committed is in need of care and protection, then, it shall, after recording the reasons in`
  line `writing, make immediate arrangement to give him such care and protection including admitting the child`
  line `into shelter home or to the nearest hospital within twenty-four hours of the report, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(6) The Special Juvenile Police Unit or local police shall, without unnecessary delay but within a`
  line `period of twenty-four hours, report the matter to the Child Welfare Committee and the Special Court or`
  line `where no Special Court has been designated, to the Court of Session, including need of the child for care`
  line `and protection and steps taken in this regard.`
  line
  line `(7) No person shall incur any liability, whether civil or criminal, for giving the information in good`
  line `faith for the purpose of sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (12869)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Obligation of media, studio and photographic facilities to report cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12869&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Any personnel of the`
  line `media or hotel or lodge or hospital or club or studio or photographic facilities, by whatever name called,`
  line `irrespective of the number of persons employed therein, shall, on coming across any material or object`
  line `which is sexually exploitative of the child (including pornographic, sexually-related or making obscene`
  line `representation of a child or children) through the use of any medium, shall provide such information to`
  line `the Special Juvenile Police Unit, or to the local police, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (12870)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Punishment for failure to report or record a case.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12870&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person, who fails to report the`
  line `commission of an offence under sub-section (1) of section 19 or section 20 or who fails to record such`
  line `offence under sub-section (2) of section 19 shall be punished with imprisonment of either description`
  line `which may extend to six months or with fine or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person, being in-charge of any company or an institution (by whatever name called) who fails`
  line `to report the commission of an offence under sub-section (1) of section 19 in respect of a subordinate`
  line `under his control, shall be punished with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year and with`
  line fine.
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall not apply to a child under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (12871)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Punishment for false complaint or false information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12871&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person, who makes false`
  line `complaint or provides false information against any person, in respect of an offence committed under`
  line `sections 3, 5, 7 and section 9, solely with the intention to humiliate, extort or threaten or defame him,`
  line `shall be punished with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months or with fine or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a false complaint has been made or false information has been provided by a child, no`
  line `punishment shall be imposed on such child.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever, not being a child, makes a false complaint or provides false information against a child,`
  line `knowing it to be false, thereby victimizing such child in any of the offences under this Act, shall be`
  line `punished with imprisonment, which may extend to one year or with fine or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (12872)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Procedure for media.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12872&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall make any report or present comments on any child`
  line `from any form of media or studio or photographic facilities without having complete and authentic`
  line `information, which may have the effect of lowering his reputation or infringing upon his privacy.`
  line
  line `(2) No reports in any media shall disclose, the identity of a child including his name, address,`
  line `photograph, family details, school, neighbourhood or any other particulars which may lead to disclosure`
  line `of identity of the child:`
  line
  line `Provided that for reasons to be recorded in writing, the Special Court, competent to try the case under`
  line `the Act, may permit such disclosure, if in its opinion such disclosure is in the interest of the child.`
  line
  line `(3) The publisher or owner of the media or studio or photographic facilities shall be jointly and`
  line `severally liable for the acts and omissions of his employee.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person who contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall be liable to`
  line `be punished with imprisonment of either description for a period which shall not be less than six months`
  line `but which may extend to one year or with fine or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (12873)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Recording of statement of a child.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12873&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The statement of the child shall be recorded at the`
  line `residence of the child or at a place where he usually resides or at the place of his choice and as far as`
  line `practicable by a woman police officer not below the rank of sub-inspector.`
  line
  line `(2) The police officer while recording the statement of the child shall not be in uniform.`
  line
  line `(3) The police officer making the investigation, shall, while examining the child, ensure that at no`
  line `point of time the child come in the contact in any way with the accused.`
  line
  line `(4) No child shall be detained in the police station in the night for any reason.`
  line
  line `(5) The police officer shall ensure that the identity of the child is protected from the public media,`
  line `unless otherwise directed by the Special Court in the interest of the child.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (12874)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Recording of statement of a child by Magistrate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12874&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the statement of the child is being`
  line `recorded under section 164 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) (herein referred to as the`
  line `Code), the Magistrate recording such statement shall, notwithstanding anything contained therein, record`
  line `the statement as spoken by the child:`
  line
  line `Provided that the provisions contained in the first proviso to sub-section (1) of section 164 of the`
  line `Code shall, so far it permits the presence of the advocate of the accused shall not apply in this case.`
  line
  line `(2) The Magistrate shall provide to the child and his parents or his representative, a copy of the`
  line `document specified under section 207 of the Code, upon the final report being filed by the police under`
  line `section 173 of that Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (12875)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Additional provisions regarding statement to be recorded.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12875&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Magistrate or the police`
  line `officer, as the case may be, shall record the statement as spoken by the child in the presence of the parents`
  line `of the child or any other person in whom the child has trust or confidence.`
  line
  line `(2) Wherever necessary, the Magistrate or the police officer, as the case may be, may take the`
  line `assistance of a translator or an interpreter, having such qualifications, experience and on payment of such`
  line `fees as may be prescribed, while recording the statement of the child.`
  line
  line `(3) The Magistrate or the police officer, as the case may be, may, in the case of a child having a`
  line `mental or physical disability, seek the assistance of a special educator or any person familiar with the`
  line `manner of communication of the child or an expert in that field, having such qualifications, experience`
  line `and on payment of such fees as may be prescribed, to record the statement of the child.`
  line
  line `(4) Wherever possible, the Magistrate or the police officer, as the case may be, shall ensure that the`
  line `statement of the child is also recorded by audio-video electronic means.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (12876)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Medical examination of a child.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12876&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The medical examination of a child in respect of whom`
  line `any offence has been committed under this Act, shall, notwithstanding that a First Information Report or`
  line `complaint has not been registered for the offences under this Act, be conducted in accordance with`
  line `section 164A of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1973).`
  line
  line `(2) In case the victim is a girl child, the medical examination shall be conducted by a woman doctor.`
  line
  line `(3) The medical examination shall be conducted in the presence of the parent of the child or any other`
  line `person in whom the child reposes trust or confidence.`
  line
  line `(4) Where, in case the parent of the child or other person referred to in sub-section (3) cannot be`
  line `present, for any reason, during the medical examination of the child, the medical examination shall be`
  line `conducted in the presence of a woman nominated by the head of the medical institution.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (12877)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Designation of Special Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12877&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of providing a speedy trial, the State`
  line `Government shall in consultation with the Chief Justice of the High Court, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, designate for each district, a Court of Session to be a Special Court to try the offences under the`
  line `Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that if a Court of Session is notified as a children's court under the Commissions for`
  line `Protection of Child Rights Act, 2005 (4 of 2006) or a Special Court designated for similar purposes under`
  line `any other law for the time being in force, then, such court shall be deemed to be a Special Court under`
  line `this section.`
  line
  line `(2) While trying an offence under this Act, a Special Court shall also try an offence [other than the`
  line `offence referred to in subsection (1)], with which the accused may, under the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) be charged at the same trial.`
  line
  line `(3) The Special Court constituted under this Act, notwithstanding anything in the Information`
  line `Technology Act, 2000 (21 of 2000) shall have jurisdiction to try offences under section 67B of that Act in`
  line `so far as it relates to publication or transmission of sexually explicit material depicting children in any act,`
  line `or conduct or manner or facilitates abuse of children online.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (12878)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Presumption as to certain offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12878&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Where a person is prosecuted for committing or abetting`
  line `or attempting to commit any offence under sections 3, 5, 7 and section 9 of this Act, the Special Court`
  line `shall presume, that such person has committed or abetted or attempted to commit the offence, as the case`
  line `may be unless the contrary is proved.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (12879)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Presumption of culpable mental state.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12879&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) In any prosecution for any offence under this Act`
  line `which requires a culpable mental state on the part of the accused, the Special Court shall presume the`
  line `existence of such mental state but it shall be a defence for the accused to prove the fact that he had no`
  line `such mental state with respect to the act charged as an offence in that prosecution.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section, a fact is said to be proved only when the Special Court believes it`
  line `to exist beyond reasonable doubt and not merely when its existence is established by a preponderance of`
  line probability.
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section, "culpable mental state" includes intention, motive, knowledge of a fact`
  line `and the belief in, or reason to believe, a fact.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (12880)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Application of Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 to proceedings before a Special Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12880&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of`
  line `1974) (including the provisions as to bail and bonds) shall apply to the proceedings before a Special Court`
  line `and for the purposes of the said provisions, the Special Court shall be deemed to be a court of Sessions`
  line `and the person conducting a prosecution before a Special Court, shall be deemed to be a Public`
  line Prosecutor.
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (12881)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Special Public Prosecutors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12881&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, appoint a Special Public Prosecutor for every Special Court for conducting cases only under the`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) A person shall be eligible to be appointed as a Special Public Prosecutor under sub-section (1)`
  line `only if he had been in practice for not less than seven years as an advocate.`
  line
  line `(3) Every person appointed as a Special Public Prosecutor under this section shall be deemed to be a`
  line `Public Prosecutor within the meaning of clause (u) of section 2 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973`
  line `(2 of 1974) and provision of that Code shall have effect accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (12882)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Procedure and powers of Special Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12882&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Special Court may take cognizance of any`
  line `offence, without the accused being committed to it for trial, upon receiving a complaint of facts which`
  line `constitute such offence, or upon a police report of such facts.`
  line
  line `(2) The Special Public Prosecutor, or as the case may be, the counsel appearing for the accused shall,`
  line `while recording the examination-in-chief, cross-examination or re-examination of the child, communicate`
  line `the questions to be put to the child to the Special Court which shall in turn put those questions to the`
  line child.
  line
  line `(3) The Special Court may, if it considers necessary, permit frequent breaks for the child during the`
  line trial.
  line
  line `(4) The Special Court shall create a child-friendly atmosphere by allowing a family member, a`
  line `guardian, a friend or a relative, in whom the child has trust or confidence, to be present in the court.`
  line
  line `(5) The Special Court shall ensure that the child is not called repeatedly to testify in the court.`
  line
  line `(6) The Special Court shall not permit aggressive questioning or character assassination of the child`
  line `and ensure that dignity of the child is maintained at all times during the trial.`
  line
  line `(7) The Special Court shall ensure that the identity of the child is not disclosed at any time during the`
  line `course of investigation or trial:`
  line
  line `Provided that for reasons to be recorded in writing, the Special Court may permit such disclosure, if`
  line `in its opinion such disclosure is in the interest of the child.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, the identity of the child shall include the identity`
  line `of the child's family, school, relatives, neighbourhood or any other information by which the identity of`
  line `the child may be revealed.`
  line
  line `(8) In appropriate cases, the Special Court may, in addition to the punishment, direct payment of such`
  line `compensation as may be prescribed to the child for any physical or mental trauma caused to him or for`
  line `immediate rehabilitation of such child.`
  line
  line `(9) Subject to the provisions of this Act, a Special Court shall, for the purpose of the trial of any`
  line `offence under this Act, have all the powers of a Court of Session and shall try such offence as if it were a`
  line `Court of Session, and as far as may be, in accordance with the procedure specified in the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) for trial before a Court of Session.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (12883)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Procedure in case of commission of offence by child and determination of age by Special Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12883&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any offence under this Act is committed by a child, such child shall be dealt with`
  line `under the provisions of ^1[the Juvenile Justice (Care and Protection of Children) Act, 2015 (2 of 2016)].`
  line
  line `(2) If any question arises in any proceeding before the Special Court whether a person is a child or`
  line `not, such question shall be determined by the Special Court after satisfying itself about the age of such`
  line `person and it shall record in writing its reasons for such determination.`
  line
  line `(3) No order made by the Special Court shall be deemed to be invalid merely by any subsequent proof`
  line `that the age of a personas determined by it under sub-section (2) was not the correct age of that person.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 2019, s. 9, for "the Juvenile Justice (Care and Protection of Children) Act, 2000 (56 of 2000)" (w.e.f. 16-`
  line `08-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (12884)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Period for recording of evidence of child and disposal of case.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12884&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The evidence of the child`
  line `shall be recorded within a period of thirty days of the Special Court taking cognizance of the offence and`
  line `reasons for delay, if any, shall be recorded by the Special Court.`
  line
  line `(2) The Special Court shall complete the trial, as far as possible, within a period of one year from the`
  line `date of taking cognizance of the offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (12885)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Child not to see accused at the time of testifying.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12885&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Special Court shall ensure that the`
  line `child is not exposed in any way to the accused at the time of recording of the evidence, while at the same`
  line `time ensuring that the accused is in a position to hear the statement of the child and communicate with his`
  line advocate.
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1), the Special Court may record the statement of a child through`
  line `video conferencing or by utilising single visibility mirrors or curtains or any other device.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (12886)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Trials to be conducted in camera.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12886&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `The Special Court shall try cases in camera and in the`
  line `presence of the parents of the child or any other person in whom the child has trust or confidence:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Special Court is of the opinion that the child needs to be examined at a place`
  line `other than the court, it shall proceed to issue a commission in accordance with the provisions of section`
  line `284 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (12887)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Assistance of an interpreter or expert while recording evidence of child.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12887&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) wherever`
  line `necessary, the Court may take the assistance of a translator or interpreter having such qualifications,`
  line `experience and on payment of such fees as may be prescribed, while recording the evidence of the child.`
  line
  line `(2) If a child has a mental or physical disability, the Special Court may take the assistance of a special`
  line `educator or any person familiar with the manner of communication of the child or an expert in that field, having such qualifications, experience and on payment of such fees as may be prescribed to record the`
  line `evidence of the child.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (12888)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Guidelines for child to take assistance of experts, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12888&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `Subject to such rules as may be made`
  line `in this behalf, the State Government shall prepare guidelines for use of non-governmental organisations,`
  line `professionals and experts or persons having knowledge of psychology, social work, physical health,`
  line `mental health and child development to be associated with the pre-trial and trial stage to assist the child.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (12889)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Right of child to take assistance of legal practitioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12889&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the proviso to section 301 of`
  line `the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) the family or the guardian of the child shall be entitled`
  line `to the assistance of a legal counsel of their choice for any offence under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the family or the guardian of the child are unable to afford a legal counsel, the Legal`
  line `Services Authority shall provide a lawyer to them.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (12890)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Provisions of sections 3 to 13 not to apply in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12890&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of sections 3 to 13`
  line `(both inclusive) shall not apply in case of medical examination or medical treatment of a child when such`
  line `medical examination or medical treatment is undertaken with the consent of his parents or guardian.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (12891)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Alternative punishment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12891&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `^1[42. Alternate punishment.-- Where an act or omission constitutes an offence punishable under this`
  line `Act and also under sections 166A, 354A, 354B, 354C, 354D, 370, 370A, 375, 376, ^2[376A, 376AB,`
  line `376B, 376C, 376D, 376DA, 376DB],`
  line `^3[376E, section 509 of the Indian Penal Code or section 67B of the`
  line `Information Technology Act, 2000 (21 of 2000)], then, notwithstanding anything contained in any law for`
  line `the time being in force, the offender found guilty of such offence shall be liable to punishment only under`
  line `this Act or under the Indian Penal Code as provides for punishment which is greater in degree.]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Arunachal Pradesh.--`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 42.--In section 42 of the Protection of Children Act, 2012 for the words`
  line `figures and letters sections 166A, 354A, 354B, 354C, 354D, 370, 370A, 375, 376, 376A, 376C, 376D,`
  line `376E or section 509 of the Indian Penal Code the words figures and letters sections 166A 354A, 354B,`
  line `354C, 354D, 370, 370A, 375, 376, 376A, 376AA, 376C, 376D, 376DA, 376E or section 509 of the Indian`
  line `Penal Code shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Arunachal Pradesh Act 3 of 2019, s. 26]`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2013, s. 29, for s. 42 (w.e.f. 3-2-2013).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 22 of 2018, s. 25, for "376A, 376C, 376D" (w.e.f. 21-4-2018)`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 2019, s. 10, for "376E or section 509 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860)" (w.e.f. 16-08-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_42_a:
  sectionId (12892)
  sectionNo 42A
  orderNo 43
  title `Act not in derogation of any other law.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2013, s. 29, for s. 42 (w.e.f. 3-2-2013).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12892&sectionno=42A&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_42_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[42A. Act not in derogation of any other law.The provisions of this Act shall be in addition to and`
  line `not in derogation of the provisions of any other law for the time being in force and, in case of any`
  line `inconsistency, the provisions of this Act shall have overriding effect on the provisions of any such law to`
  line `the extent of the inconsistency.]`
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (12893)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 44
  title `Public awareness about Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12893&sectionno=43&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government and every State Government, shall take`
  line `all measures to ensure that--`
  line
  line `(a) the provisions of this Act are given wide publicity through media including the television,`
  line `radio and the print media at regular intervals to make the general public, children as well as their`
  line `parents and guardians aware of the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) the officers of the Central Government and the State Governments and other concerned`
  line `persons (including the police officers) are imparted periodic training on the matters relating to the`
  line `implementation of the provisions of the Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (12894)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 45
  title `Monitoring of implementation of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12894&sectionno=44&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Commission for Protection of Child`
  line `Rights constituted under section 3, or as the case may be, the State Commission for Protection of Child`
  line `Rights constituted under section 17, of the Commissions for Protection of Child Rights Act, 2005 (4 of`
  line `2006) shall, in addition to the functions assigned to them under that Act, also monitor the implementation`
  line `of the provisions of this Act in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The National Commission or, as the case may be, the State Commission, referred to in sub-section`
  line `(1), shall, while inquiring into any matter relating to any offence under this Act, have the same powers as`
  line `are vested in it under the Commissions for Protection of Child Rights Act, 2005 (4 of 2006).`
  line
  line `(3) The National Commission or, as the case may be, the State Commission, referred to in sub-section`
  line `(1), shall, also include, its activities under this section, in the annual report referred to in section 16 of the`
  line `Commissions for Protection of Child Rights Act, 2005 (4 of 2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (12895)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 46
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12895&sectionno=45&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) the manner of deleting or destroying or reporting about pornographic material in any form`
  line `involving a child to the designated authority under sub-section (1) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(aa) the manner of reporting about pornographic material in any form involving a child under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 15;]`
  line
  line `^2[(ab)] the qualifications and experience of, and the fees payable to, a translator or an interpreter,`
  line `a special educator or any person familiar with the manner of communication of the child or an expert`
  line `in that field, under sub-section (4) of section 19; sub-sections(2) and (3) of section 26 and section 38;`
  line
  line `(b) care and protection and emergency medical treatment of the child under sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 19;`
  line
  line `(c) the payment of compensation under sub-section (8) of section 33;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner of periodic monitoring of the provisions of the Act under sub-section (1) of`
  line section44.
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 25 of 2019, s. 11 (w.e.f. 16-08-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Clause (a) re-lettered as clause (ab) thereof by Act 25 of 2019, s. 11 (w.e.f. 16-08-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (12896)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 47
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686&sectionId=12896&sectionno=46&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00005_201232_1517807323686
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as may appear to it to be necessary or expedient for`
  line `removal of the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of the period of two years`
  line `from the commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
